===== HOW TO submit jobs for the Muon Geometric efficiency ===


2. Muon Geometric Efficiency

-- again here we use as input the files obtained from the Hadron Geometric Efficiency step
2.0 make a working directory, i.e SubmitMuonEffJobs
cd SubmitMuonEffJobs

2.1 put in FDCAFs.txt all the existent FDOutput files obtained from hadron geom efficiency
ls -d "PATHToMYFDHadronEffOutputFiles"/* | sed "s\/pnfs\root://fndca1.fnal.gov:1094/pnfs/fnal.gov/usr\g" > FDCAFs.txt
where PATHToMYFDHadronEffOutputFiles is the path where you saved your output files from the hadron geo eff

2.2 Get the work env setup: -- you find it either at /exp/dune/app/users/icaracas/NDEff/DUNE_PRISM_GEC_ND/code or at https://github.com/icaracas/DUNE_ND_GeoEff/tree/MuonCode
you need : setup_NDcombEff.sh, run_FDcombEff.sh, FD_maketree.py, muonEff30.nn, muonEffModel.py

Things you might want to change:
- in run_FDcombEff.sh: output directory where your files are saved; now it is OUTDIR=/pnfs/dune/scratch/users/${GRID_USER}/FDGeoEffinND/MuonEff/Resub -> you might want to make your own named directory etc

2.3 make the tarball
tar -czvf FD_work.tar.gz setup_NDcombEff.sh FD_maketree.py muonEff30.nn muonEffModel.py FDCAFs.txt

2.4 Submit the job:
# You can use ```wc -l FDCAFs.txt``` to check the number of files in txt file
# this is example is for 9635 files in FDCAFs.txt, so 9635 jobs
jobsub_submit -G dune -N 9635 --memory=5GB --disk=15GB --expected-lifetime=8h --cpu=1 --resource-provides=usage_model=DEDICATED,OPPORTUNISTIC,OFFSITE --tar_file_name=dropbox:///exp/dune/app/users/icaracas/NDEff/DUNE_PRISM_GEC_ND/code/FD_work.tar.gz --use-cvmfs-dropbox -l '+SingularityImage=\"/cvmfs/singularity.opensciencegrid.org/fermilab/fnal-wn-sl7:latest\"' --append_condor_requirements='(TARGET.HAS_Singularity==true&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_dune_opensciencegrid_org==true&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_larsoft_opensciencegrid_org==true&&TARGET.CVMFS_dune_opensciencegrid_org_REVISION>=1105&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_fifeuser1_opensciencegrid_org==true&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_fifeuser2_opensciencegrid_org==true&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_fifeuser3_opensciencegrid_org==true&&TARGET.HAS_CVMFS_fifeuser4_opensciencegrid_org==true)' file:///exp/dune/app/users/icaracas/NDEff/DUNE_PRISM_GEC_ND/code/run_FDcombEff.sh

-- again remember to replace  /exp/dune/app/users/icaracas/NDEff/DUNE_PRISM_GEC_ND/code/ in the job submission with your working folder (i.e same folder where you created FDCAFs.txt and the tar file) -- directory from point 2.0
